The article emphasizes the need for global cooperation in response to the COVID-19 pandemic and the growing threat of biological risks. It highlights the devastating impact of infectious diseases and calls for enhanced biopreparedness, biosafety, and biosecurity worldwide. The United States aims to strengthen and revitalize the Biological Weapons Convention (BWC) to prevent the development and use of biological weapons. The article urges all countries to take the threat of biological weapons seriously and proposes practical measures to counter biological threats and benefit BWC members. The United States is committed to working with other nations to achieve global health security for everyone.